The paper discusses a problem in the belief functions theory and proposes a new combination rule to solve it. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of unification rules and discounting procedures, which are common in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with specificity in expert responses, which could fall under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
